This paper deals with compressed sensing of sparse sources, which is a topic that falls under multiple sub-categories in arXiv CS. 

- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category as it deals with the theory and algorithms for efficient information processing, including compressed sensing. 
- cs.SP (Signal Processing) is also a likely sub-category as it deals with the analysis and processing of signals, including compressed sensing. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category as it deals with the development of algorithms that can learn from data, including compressed sensing. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a possible sub-category as it deals with the analysis and processing of visual data, which can be compressed using sparse representations. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible sub-category as it deals with the processing and analysis of multimedia data, including compressed sensing.
